package.json 
> Meta Data (name,version,description)
> Packages 
> script (start,test)
> This is the first file app 

///////////////////
Step to generate Package.json 
//////////////////////
* Nodejs must be install in your system
> Go Inside the folder using cmd 
> type npm init 
> Answer all questions
> type "yes"

/////////////////////
Local Dependency  > local to the folder 
Global Dependency > local to the system
Dev Dependency    > Use only at the time of development 


///////////////////
Step to install Local Dependency
//////////////////////
* Nodejs must be install in your system
> Go Inside the folder using cmd 
> npm i package name / npm i package name  --save



///////////////////
Step to install Dev Dependency
//////////////////////
* Nodejs must be install in your system
> Go Inside the folder using cmd 
> npm i package name  --save-dev 

///////////////////
Step to install Global Dependency
//////////////////////
> install in the system directly 
> will not add on package.json 
> we need admin access to install 
> only packages help to generate or run app will go global

#Window
> open cmd as admin 
> npm i -g packagename

#mac/linux
> open terminal
> sudo npm i -g packagename


npm init -y 